cytoscape.hyperedge.impl
Class HyperEdgeManagerImpl

java.lang.Object
  cytoscape.hyperedge.impl.HyperEdgeManagerImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
HyperEdgeManager
public class HyperEdgeManagerImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements HyperEdgeManager

Singleton object implementation of the HyperEdgeManager interface.

Unmodifiable Iterator Return Values

Several HyperEdgeManager operations return unmodifiable iterators as return values (e.g., HyperEdgeManager.getHyperEdgesByNode()). Creation of all these iterators is done using HEUtils.buildUnmodifiableCollectionIterator(). These iterators have certain properties that should be understood. Please see this method for details.

Version:
2.0
Author:
Michael L. Creech

Clear out the contents of this HyperEdgeManager. All HyperEdges, and CyEdges are removed.

Specified by:
reset in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
fireEvents - if true, HyperEdges will be removed in such a way that DeleteListener.objectDestroyed() events are fired at the expense of being slower to reset. If false, no objectDestroyed() events are fired, but resetting will be faster.

getHyperEdgesByNode

public java.util.Iterator<HyperEdge> getHyperEdgesByNode(cytoscape.CyNode node,
                                                         cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeManager
Return an Iterator over all HyperEdges containing CyEdges that connect to a given CyNode, for a given CyNetwork. Only the non-ConnectorNode endpoints of all the CyEdges contained by the HyperEdge are considered.

Specified by:
getHyperEdgesByNode in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
node - the CyNode that must be connected to the non-ConnectorNode endpoint of a CyEdge that is a member of a HyperEdge. If null, node is not considered in the matching process and all HyperEdges satisfying net are returned.
net - the CyNetwork within which the HyperEdge must belong. If null, all HyperEdges satisfying node are returned.
Returns:
a non-null, read-only Iterator (doesn't allow modification) over all matching HyperEdges. The iterator will contain all existing HyperEdges if both node and net are null. The Iterator will be empty if no HyperEdge contains node, or if no HyperEdge within the given non-null net contains the node.

Return an Iterator over all HyperEdges containing a collection of CyNodes for a given CyNetwork. Only the non-ConnectorNode endpoints of all the CyEdges contained by the HyperEdge are considered.

Specified by:
getHyperEdgesByNodes in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:

getHyperEdgesByEdgeTypes

public java.util.Iterator<HyperEdge> getHyperEdgesByEdgeTypes(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> edgeITypes,
                                                              cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeManager
Return an Iterator over all HyperEdges containing CyNodes with CyEdges that match a given Collection of edge interaction types within a given CyNetwork.

Specified by:
getHyperEdgesByEdgeTypes in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
edgeITypes - the Collection of String edge interaction types where each edge interaction type must match the interaction type attribute of a CyEdge contained within the HyperEdge. If null, edgeITypes are not considered in the matching process and all HyperEdges satisfying net are returned.
net - the CyNetwork within which the HyperEdges must belong. If null, all HyperEdges satisfying edgeITypes are returned.
Returns:
a non-null, read-only Iterator (doesn't allow modification) over all matching HyperEdges. A HyperEdge matches iff for every edge interaction type in edgeITypes, there is a corresponding CyEdge whose interaction type attribute matches edge type. The iterator will contain all existing HyperEdges if both edgeITypes and net are null. Iterator will be empty if no HyperEdge contains nodes that coorespond to the given edgeITypes, or if no HyperEdge within the given non-null net contains nodes that coorespond to the given edgeITypes.

getNodesByEdgeTypes

public java.util.Iterator<cytoscape.CyNode> getNodesByEdgeTypes(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> edgeITypes,
                                                                cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeManager
Return an Iterator over all distinct CyNodes associated with HyperEdge CyEdges that match any of a given Collection of edge types and are found within a given CyNetwork. The CyNodes returned are the CyNodes connected to the non-ConnectorNode endpoint of each CyEdge.

Specified by:
getNodesByEdgeTypes in interface HyperEdgeManager
Parameters:
edgeITypes - the Collection of String edge interaction types where at least one edge type must match the type of a CyEdge associated with a given CyNode. If null, edgeITypes are not considered in the matching process and all CyNodes satisfying net are returned.
net - the CyNetwork within which the HyperEdges must belong. If null, the CyNetwork is not considered in the matching process and all CyNodes satisfying edgeITypes are returned.
Returns:
a non-null, read-only Iterator (doesn't allow modification) over all distinct matching CyNodes. A CyNode matches iff for at least one edge interaction type in edgeITypes, there is a corresponding CyEdge associated with this CyNode whose interaction type attribute matches edge type. The iterator will contain all CyNodes found within any HyperEdge if both edgeITypes and net are null. Iterator will be empty if edgeITypes is empty, no CyNode cooresponds to the given edgeITypes, or if no CyNode within the given non-null net contains CyNodes that coorespond to the given edgeITypes.

hideConnectorNodes

public void hideConnectorNodes(cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
A hack needed to handle deletion of ConnectorNodes. Will hide all ConnectorNodes on the internal hidden ConnectorNode list for a given Cynetwork. If (when) HyperEdges are added to the Cytoscape core, this can be removed. See details on this in How Do We Keep HyperEdge Structures Up-To_Date? in http://cytoscape.wodaklab.org/wiki/HyperEdgeUpdating.

hideConnectorNodes

public void hideConnectorNodes()
A hack needed to handle deletion of ConnectorNodes. Will hide all ConnectorNodes on the internal hidden ConnectorNode list for all CyNetworks. If (when) HyperEdges are added to the Cytoscape core, this can be removed. See details on this in How Do We Keep HyperEdge Structures Up-To_Date? in http://cytoscape.wodaklab.org/wiki/HyperEdgeUpdating.

intersection

public static java.util.List<HyperEdge> intersection(java.util.List<HyperEdge> a,
                                                     java.util.List<HyperEdge> b)
Return a non-null List of the HyperEdges that intersect two given lists. This method is thread-safe.

Parameters:
a - a List of HyperEdgeImpls.
b - a List of HyperEdgeImpls.
Returns:
the empty list if a or b is null, or if no intersections are found. Otherwise, return the list of intersecting HyperEdges.
